<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14906">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Motorboating.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14907">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14907 mb-requirement-id-14908">
        (a) Discuss with your counselor the following hazards you might
        encounter while motorboating: flammable fuel; carbon monoxide;
        propellers; collisions; falls overboard; capsize; or running aground.
        Explain what you should do to anticipate, prevent, mitigate and respond
        to these hazards. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tQ3cHcqV_8A" target="_blank"
          >Running Aground Prevention and Response (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gaZQc_trnCs" target="_blank"
          >Towsport Tips #4 Carbon Monoxide (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TVD0LxihhR8" target="_blank"
          >Collision Avoidance Rules (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Sj2iIZgXRxk" target="_blank"
          >Preventing a Capsizing / Fall Overboard (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14907 mb-requirement-id-14909">
        (b) Explain first aid for injuries or illnesses that could occur while
        motorboating, including hypothermia, heat reactions, dehydration, motion
        sickness, bug bites, blisters. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rH3gZuSr6Y8" target="_blank"
          >Cold Water Shock—How to Deal With Cold Water Shock (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EmNieKLjmH4" target="_blank"
          >What Happens If You Don't Drink Enough Water? Signs of Dehydration +
          4 Ways to Keep Hydrated (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Rz6Wxiv4aRA" target="_blank"
          >Mayo Clinic Minute—Dangers of Heat-Related Illnesses (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://paddlingmag.com/skills/how-to-prevent-and-treat-blisters/"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Prevent and Treat Blisters (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14907 mb-requirement-id-14910">
        (c) Discuss the Scouting America Safety Afloat policy. Tell how it
        applies to motorboating activities. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/safety-afloat/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Afloat (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14911">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14911 mb-requirement-id-14912">
        (a) Before doing requirement 5, successfully complete the Scouting
        America swimmer test.<br /><br /><b>Note:</b> See the
        <i>Swimming </i>merit badge pamphlet for details about the Scouting
        America swimmer test. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Swimming.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          ><i>Swimming</i> Merit Badge pamphlet (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14911 mb-requirement-id-14913">
        (b) Name the different types of personal flotation devices (PFDs), and
        explain when each type should be used. Show how to choose and properly
        fit a PFD. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4y9XPNy1L1U" target="_blank"
          >How To Choose the Right Life Jacket (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14914">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14914 mb-requirement-id-14915">
        (a) Explain inboard, outboard, and inboard/outboard motors, and the uses
        and advantages of each. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1U10bHSLZQ4" target="_blank"
          >Whats the Difference Between Inboard, Outboard &amp; Sterndrive Boat
          Engines? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KNOmP3Z8YKg" target="_blank"
          >Engine Types (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14914 mb-requirement-id-14916">
        (b) Explain the safety procedures and precautions involving handling
        fuel and engine servicing, and equipment storage and placement. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0LAyvXOn_Ug" target="_blank"
          >Fueling Procedures (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.boat-ed.com/indiana/studyGuide/Engine-Maintenance/10101602_35162"
          target="_blank"
          >Engine Servicing (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14914 mb-requirement-id-14917">
        (c) Explain how to winterize a boat motor and tell why this procedure is
        necessary. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5LLUFFq9zgA" target="_blank"
          >Winterize Your Boat Like a Pro in 7 Steps (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14914 mb-requirement-id-14918">
        (d) Explain the safety procedures and precautions involving swimmers and
        skiers in the water, passenger positions underway, and boat wakes.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/h6KbCnRXkyM" target="_blank"
          >Boat Wakes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14919">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Show you know safety guidelines for motorboating by doing the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14919 mb-requirement-id-14920">
        (a) Review how each item of the Scouting America Safety Afloat policy
        applies, including checking the weather prior to and during time on the
        water, confirming all required equipment is present and functional, and
        following a float plan.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14919 mb-requirement-id-14921">
        (b) Explain the rules or laws that apply to recreational boating in your
        area or state. Have a permit to operate a motorboat, if required by the
        laws of your state. Discuss how you would find information regarding the
        boating laws in different states. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.discoverboating.com/ownership/safety/boating-rules-and-regulations-by-state"
          target="_blank"
          >Boating Rules and Regulations by State (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14919 mb-requirement-id-14922">
        (c) Discuss how hazards of weather and heavy water conditions can affect
        safety and performance in motorboating. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pigz13CeesU" target="_blank"
          >Foul Weather Boating (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vbCSQyOPvbE" target="_blank"
          >Coping With Foul Weather (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/6_Q_1_jyHuY" target="_blank"
          >Operation in Restricted Visibility (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14919 mb-requirement-id-14923">
        (d) Promise that you will follow Scouting America Safety Afloat
        guidelines. Explain the meaning of each point.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14919 mb-requirement-id-14924">
        (e) Explain and show the correct use of equipment required by both state
        and federal regulations to be carried aboard a motorboat. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/biRTksu9ZNw" target="_blank"
          >Coast Guard Requirements: What Items You Must Have in Your Boat (ID,
          Tools, etc) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14919 mb-requirement-id-14925">
        (f) Explain federal and state rules for a ventilation system, and tell
        why these rules are required.<br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/XlhfoJt_m0U" target="_blank"
          >Ventilation Systems (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14919 mb-requirement-id-14926">
        (g) Explain the use of lights (sight signals) and sound signals on
        motorboats. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fbyeg5y_qPE" target="_blank"
          >Navigation Light Equipment (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14919 mb-requirement-id-14927">
        (h) Discuss the common types of anchors used in motorboating and under
        what conditions each would be preferred. Explain proper anchoring
        techniques. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Iv3_8a7N_aE" target="_blank"
          >Anchoring (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/tK_d6wYEsP4" target="_blank"
          >Anchoring Tips (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/3CHgH0irUIA" target="_blank"
          >Anchoring a Boat | Basics of Boating (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14928">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      With your counselor or other adults on board, demonstrate proper
      boat-handling procedures and skills by doing the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14928 mb-requirement-id-14929">
        (a) Board and assist others in boarding. Confirm that all passengers on
        board are wearing properly fitted life jackets. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/PjpUIpX5Fw8" target="_blank"
          >Boating Equipment—Personal Flotation Devices (PFDs) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/KVCNH96HqFs" target="_blank"
          >Life Jacket Safety Essentials | Discover Boating (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14928 mb-requirement-id-14930">
        (b) Fuel the boat and complete a safety check. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/NyqsxYaWJS4" target="_blank"
          >Quick Tip: Pre-Boating Inspection &amp; Safety Checklist (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14928 mb-requirement-id-14931">
        (c) If equipped, attach the engine cut-off switch link and safely start
        the motor. Get underway from dockside or from a beach launch. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/IOM4aTiH2Pc" target="_blank"
          >Launching a Boat (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14928 mb-requirement-id-14932">
        (d) Run a course for at least a mile, showing procedures for overtaking
        and passing slower vessels, yielding right-of-way, passing oncoming
        traffic, making turns, reversing direction, and using navigation aids.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/-Ozqi07qgi8" target="_blank"
          >What Every Boater Needs To Know About Boating Rules/Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14928 mb-requirement-id-14933">
        (e) Stop and secure the boat in position on the open water using
        anchors. Raise and stow the anchor and get underway.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14928 mb-requirement-id-14934">
        (f) Land or dock the boat, disembark, and assist others in doing the
        same. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7WaH87ZYBLs" target="_blank"
          >Retrieving a Boat (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14928 mb-requirement-id-14935">
        (g) Moor, dock, or beach the boat and secure all gear. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/VGfCKxv5t70" target="_blank"
          >How To Tie a Boat to a Dock (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.boatus.com/expert-advice/expert-advice-archive/2014/august/beaching-your-boat"
          target="_blank"
          >Beaching Your Boat (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-14928 mb-requirement-id-14936">
        (h) Demonstrate knots used in boating: cleating hitch, bowline, clove
        hitch, anchor bend, sheet bend. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TbJGKazU1co" target="_blank"
          >10 Knots You Need for Sailing (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pEWcxx8998U" target="_blank"
          >How To Tie the Anchor Bend Knot | Boating Knots (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
